title: @OspreyWBB Tabbed Eighth in #ASunWBB Preseason Coaches Poll
text: 2015-16 Atlantic Sun Women's Basketball Preseason Honors and Awards MACON, Ga. – University of North Florida women's basketball came in eighth in both the Atlantic Sun Preseason Coaches Poll and Preseason Media Poll, the conference announced on Thursday afternoon. Voting for the Coaches Poll was done by the Atlantic Sun's eight head coaches, while the media poll votes were from the conferences Sports Information Directors and other media members. The teams rankings in both polls were the same. UNF tallied 13 points in the Coaches Poll and 45 points in the Media Poll. Perennial Atlantic Sun powerhouse FGCU topped both polls. The Eagles received all eight first-place votes from the coaches for 64 points and claimed 22 first-place votes and 183 points in the media poll. Stetson came in second with 52 points in the Coaches Poll and tallied 153 point and one first-place vote in the media poll. Jacksonville was third (46 points – coaches, 125 – media) and Kenensaw State was fourth (44 points – coaches, 108 – media). USC Upstate came in fifth with 33 points in the Coaches Poll and 88 in the Media Poll. Lipscomb tallied 20 points in the Coaches Poll and 70 in the media for a six-place ranking. Atlantic Sun newcomer NJIT came in seventh (16 points – coaches, 56 – media). UNF begins the 2015-16 season on Friday, Nov. 13 at UMKC. Tip-off is set for 2 p.m.
